==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Indo-European ''*tū''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[thu]], Old Saxon ''þu'' (Low German [[du]]), Old High German [[thu|thū]] (German [[du]]), Old Norse [[þú]], Gothic [[𐌸𐌿]], Latin [[tu]] (French [[tu]]), Greek [[συ]], Lithuanian [[tu|tù]], Russian [[ты]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ðu:/

===Personal pronoun===
'''þū'''
# [[thou]]

